Argentine Stocks: Banco Hipotecario, Siderar and YPF

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-09-12T20:19:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-12/argentine-stocks-banco-hipotecario-siderar-and-ypf.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The Merval Index fell 2.4 percent to 2,688.06.  Banco Hipotecario SA (BHIP)   retreated 6 percent to 1.73
pesos, its lowest price in a year. The price of sovereign bonds
fell today in  Argentina , which signals lower value for banks’
fixed-income holdings.  Siderar SAIC (ERAR)   fell 4.1 percent to 24.45 pesos.
Argentina’s largest steel producer dropped in line with base
metal prices, which declined on concern  Europe ’s sovereign-debt
crisis is deepening.  YPF SA (YPFD)   dropped 2.3 percent to 170 pesos, its
second day of losses. Argentina’s largest crude producer
extended an option to buy a stake in BG Group Plc’s Metrogas SA,
Gas Argentino SA said today in an Argentine regulatory filing.
Gas Argentino is the controller of natural gas distributor
Metrogas SA.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
